[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Taraba State)
Date: Mon 28 Jul 2014
Source: Leadership [edited]
http://leadership.ng/news/379267/cholera-outbreak-kills-6-taraba


A deputy director of health in the Bali local government of the Taraba State, Mr Adamu Alura, stated yesterday, 27 Jul 2014, during an interview with journalists, that 6 people have already lost their lives from cholera while 27 others are currently receiving treatment at various hospitals in the local government.

He noted that those affected by the disease are from Bali A and B wards of the local government area.

"I have already written to the local government management for money to enable them buy drugs for the treatment of those affected by the disease," he said, adding that they have also written to the concerned authority in the state on the outbreak of the disease, while the state government has directed a senior staff at the state ministry of Environment to sensitise people on the need to observe proper hygiene.

--
