[5] Cholera - Ghana (Accra)
Date: Wed 30 Jul 2014
Source: Star Africa, Agence Africaine de Presse (APA) report [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/cholera-toll-jumps-to-five-in-ghana.html


Some parts of the Ghanaian capital of Accra are battling an outbreak of cholera which has so far killed 5 people, according to Hospital Administrator at La General Hospital Philip Afeti Korto in Accra. Mr Afeti Korto told reporters on [Tue 29 Jul 2014], over 170 cases had been reported with 5 persons losing their lives in the situation which broke out a week ago. Affected victims are reported to have come from other suburbs in the capital such as Osu, Teshie, and Nugua.

