[7] Cholera - India (West Bengal State)
Date: Tue 29 Jul 2014
Source: The Hindu [edited]
http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/cholera-outbreak-at-paschim-medinipur-in-west-bengal/article6260084.ece


As many as 13 persons, including children, with cholera symptoms were admitted to a primary health centre and nearby medical camps at Tatarpur village in Paschim Medinipur district, a medical officer said on Mon 28 Jul 2014.

"5 persons are in the hospital and the remaining has been discharged. We have found _Vibrio cholerae_ bacteria in the sample of only one person. The test for other samples is awaited," district's Chief Medical Officer (Health) Girish Chandra Bera told The Hindu over phone. Asked about the reason for the infection, Dr Bera said that those hospitalised source water from a pond in the village and the water there may be contaminated.

